# Authoritative for dup-glue.demo. The interesting bit isn't here
# (the zone is otherwise vanilla) — it's in the parent's referral,
# where demo/coredns/root/zones/demo.zone lists the same A glue
# record TWICE for this zone's NS. CoreDNS's file plugin preserves
# duplicate RRs at the wire level, which is what we want to surface
# issue #26: a parent returning duplicate glue used to inflate the
# per-server query counter via extractDelegation's un-deduped
# glueMap append. See PR linked from #26.

dup-glue.demo. {
    file /zones/dup-glue.demo.zone
    log
    errors
}
